AGI - They forced women from Romania to ask for alms in the center of Bologna and to pour them all they received, threatening them and beating them when they did not gather enough: with this accusation two Romanian citizens were arrested in Bologna for human being and slavery reduction. The State Police of the Emilian capital, in the context of an activity coordinated by the Prosecutor at the local Tribunal D.D.A., carried out the measure of the custody.
The investigation of the Bologna Mobile Team began with the complaint of two young Romanian sisters who, now exhausted, reported being recruited in 2019 by two of their compatriots in Romania, with the promise to move to Italy to carry out the work of domestics.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Once in Bologna, the two victims discovered that they had been deceived and had been forced by their compatriots to carry out acknowledging activities. On various occasions, due to an inadequate gain, young women have been violently misunderstood and threatened with repercussions on their relatives residing in Romania. In the course of the investigation, the investigators of the Mobile Team came across a third Romanian victim who on one occasion was violently misled by one of the two investigators. The victim also reported that she had come to Italy for a few years with the hope of an honest job, because of her total state of indigence, but, once she arrived, she was forced by the two inquired to carry out accompaniment, giving them the money received. Precious for the purpose of the investigation was also the testimony of an Italian woman who, on some occasions, had the opportunity to see one of the victims with unequivocal visible signs of the suffering.
&nbsp;

